On Mon, 12 May 2003, Eric Murray wrote:
> I don't think I can do an SMTP error message since its
> getting handled in procmail, after the body is accepted.

You can fake it.

lne.com forwarding all mail to eg. internal.lne.com and only the
internal.lne.com doing the rejections is a valid setup. You can use
procmail to feed the body of the rejected mail to some script that will
"forge" the bounce message and send it back.

